ide-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-complete.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102439/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-complete.jpg 1800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102439/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-complete-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102439/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-complete-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102439/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-complete-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102439/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-complete-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102439/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-complete-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102439/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-complete-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102439/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-complete-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102439/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-complete-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Most interesting of the two are the new PD-M829 Saint flat pedals, built for everything from DH racing to aggressive trail riding. They share a wide, 8-sided outer profile and body inset to extend the pedal platform all the way to the crankarm like the current M828 Saint pedals, but the similarities stop there.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Shimano lightweight Saint gravity enduro freeride DH mountain bike platform pedals, M829 detail\" width=\"1500\" height=\"844\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail.jpg 1500w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-746x420.jpg 746w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail.jpg 1500w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102448/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-angled-detail-746x420.jpg 746w\"></a></p><p>Now the new Saint pedal features a thin forged alloy (shiny polished silver AND the black under ‘INT’ which seems to be the same alloy finish as the XT pedals) body with connecting webs, sandwiched inside a ‘carbon composite resin’ element that wraps over the front, rear, and outside of the pedal. Shimano calls it a ‘carbon skid plate’ for the thin aluminum body, designed to slip &amp; slide over rocks on the trail.</p><p>Shimano says the new Saint DH pedals offer ‘best-in-class grip’ with 10 traction pins around the perimeter, 4 more optional pins in the middle,&nbsp;and a thin double-concave design. The 121mm long x 110mm wide Saint pedals are 16.1mm thick at the front &amp; rear edges, 13.9mm thick at the inside &amp; outside, and just 11.6mm thin in the middle.</p><figure id=\"attachment_267003\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-267003\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102456/Shimano-lightweight-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M829-top.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.c