umor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102428/Shimano-lightweight-XT-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M8141-top-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102428/Shimano-lightweight-XT-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M8141-top-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102428/Shimano-lightweight-XT-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M8141-top-1920x1440.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102428/Shimano-lightweight-XT-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M8141-top-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102428/Shimano-lightweight-XT-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M8141-top-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102428/Shimano-lightweight-XT-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_M8141-top-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-267000\">Shimano XT platform pedals, PD-M8141</figcaption></figure><p>The XTs also feature a thin double-concave design 17.5mm front/back, 17.2mm side/side &amp; 13.3mm in the middle, and they share the same durable chromoly axle with new ‘bushing construction’. XTs also get the same 10 outer pin placement, plus 2 more optional inboard pins, as well.</p><p>The all-alloy XT M8141 platform pedals still weigh just 428g, a savings of 78g over the&nbsp;bulky current M8140 XTs (and 31g heavier than the new Saints.)</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/30102410/Shimano-lightweight-XT-Saint-gravity-enduro-freeride-DH-mountain-bike-platform-pedals_flat-pedal-so